{{Infobox person |name=Allison Williams |image=Allison Williams July 2012.jpg |alt= |caption=Williams in July 2012 |birth_name=Allison Howell Williams<ref>{{cite web|author1=Adam Sachs|title=Allison Williams on Her Brand-New Blonde, Daily Doughnuts, and Her Pal Katy Perry|url=https://www.allure.com/story/allison-williams-interview-march-2017|accessdate=November 2, 2017|date=February 8, 2017|quote=I think if I’d used my middle name professionally—Howell Williams—I’d have a totally different career.}}</ref> |birth_date={{birth date and age|1988|4|13}} |birth_place=[[New Canaan, Connecticut]], U.S. |alma_mater=[[Yale University]] |occupation=Actress, comedian, singer |years_active=2004–present |residence=[[Chelsea, Manhattan|Chelsea, New York]] |spouse={{Marriage|[[Ricky Van Veen]]|September 19, 2015}} |parents=[[Brian Williams]] }} '''Allison Howell Williams''' (born April 13, 1988)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/2014/04/13/4053609/celebrity-birthdays-on-april-13.html |title=Celebrity birthdays on April 13 |work=[[The Miami Herald]] |date=April 13, 2014 |accessdate=July 6, 2014| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140416182352/http://www.miamiherald.com/2014/04/13/4053609/celebrity-birthdays-on-april-13.html | archivedate= April 16, 2014| quote=Actress Allison Williams ('Girls') is 26.}}</ref> is an American actress, comedian, and singer. She is best known for her role as Marnie Michaels on the [[HBO]] [[comedy-drama]] series ''[[Girls (TV series)|Girls]]'' and her critically acclaimed performance in the 2017 horror film ''[[Get Out]]''.
==Early life== Williams was born and raised in [[New Canaan, Connecticut]],<ref>{{cite web |first=Amy|last=Kaufman|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-allison-williams-2017-story.html |title=How Allison Williams mined the horrors of white privilege for 'Get Out' |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|publisher=[[Tronc]]|location=Los Angeles, California |date=February 17, 2017 |accessdate=August 16, 2018}}</ref> the daughter of former ''[[NBC Nightly News]]'' anchor and managing editor [[Brian Williams]]<ref name="post">{{cite news |first=Dana |last=Schuster |url=https://nypost.com/2011/08/05/anchors-away/ |title=Anchor's away |newspaper=[[New York Post]] |publisher=[[News Corp.]]|location=New York City|date=August 5, 2011 |accessdate=July 6, 2014}}</ref> and TV producer Jane Gillan Stoddard. She has a brother, Doug, three years her junior.<ref>{{cite web|first=John|last=Koblin|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/20/business/doug-brian-williams-sny.html|title=Another Williams Takes His Turn Before the Camera, at SNY|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=New York Times Company|location=New York City|date=July 20, 2017|accessdate=February 5, 2018}}</ref> She attended [[New Canaan Country School]] and [[Greenwich Academy]],<ref name=NCAdvertiser>{{cite news |url=http://ncadvertiser.com/41615/new-canaans-sweetheart-set-to-soar/|title=Allison Williams flies high|newspaper=[[New Canaan Advertiser]]|date=December 4, 2014}} *“I went to the New Canaan Nature Center for preschool,” she said. “I was so into that world, and still think about it all the time. It established my love for nature and animals.” "New Canaan Country School and Greenwich Academy followed."</ref> then graduated from [[Yale University]].<ref name="post"/> While at Yale, Williams was a member of the [[Improvisational theatre|improv]] comedy troupe [[Just Add Water (improv troupe)|Just Add Water]] for four years,<ref name="yale">{{cite web|first=Danny|last=Serna|url=https://yaledailynews.com/blog/2011/01/11/hbo-picks-up-new-television-series-starring-allison-williams-10/|title=HBO picks up new television series starring Allison Williams '10/|newspaper=[[Yale Daily News]]|publisher=[[Yale University]]|location=New Haven, Connecticut|date=January 11, 2011|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=November 16, 2017}}</ref> was involved in the [[YouTube]] series ''College Musical'',<ref>{{cite web|first=Emily A. |last=Farris |url=http://gawker.com/5590877/brian-williams-daughter-plays-sensual-ta-in-college-musical-web-series |title=Brian Williams' Daughter Plays Sensual TA in College Musical Web Series |website=[[Gawker]] |publisher=[[Gawker Media]]|location=New York City|date=July 19, 2010 |accessdate=April 16, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130417095057/http://gawker.com/5590877/brian-williams-daughter-plays-sensual-ta-in-college-musical-web-series |archivedate=April 17, 2013 |df= }}</ref> and was inducted by [[St. Elmo (secret society)|St. Elmo]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Alex |last=Klein |url=http://www.ivygateblog.com/2010/05/web-exclusive-every-yale-secret-society-2008-2009-or-a-tribute-to-rumpus/ |title=''WEB EXCLUSIVE'': Every Yale Secret Society, 2009–2010 (or, A Tribute to ''Rumpus'') |website=[[IvyGate]] |date=May 5, 2010 |accessdate=April 26, 2012}}</ref>
==Career== In 2010, Williams performed a mashup of "[[Nature Boy]]" set to [[RJD2]]'s "A Beautiful Mine", the theme song for the television series ''[[Mad Men]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Shea |first=Danny |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/10/13/allison-williams-brian-wi_n_761128.html |title=Allison Williams, Brian Williams' Daughter, Sings 'Mad Men' Theme Song (VIDEO) |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |publisher=[[Huffington Post Media Group]]|location=New York City|date=October 13, 2010 |accessdate=December 28, 2011}}</ref> The YouTube video of the performance received widespread praise on the Internet,<ref>{{cite web |first=Rachel |last=Sklar |url=http://www.mediaite.com/online/allison-williams-this-week-the-biggest-star-in-her-family-sorry-briwi/ |title=Allison Williams, This Week The Biggest Star In Her Family (Sorry, BriWi) |website=[[Mediaite]] |date=October 14, 2010 |accessdate=December 28, 2011}}</ref> and convinced [[Judd Apatow]] that she should be given a part in the [[HBO]] series ''[[Girls (TV series)|Girls]]''.<ref name="post"/> She was cast shortly after and credited her experience at Just Add Water for passing the audition.<ref name="yale"/><ref>{{cite web |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva|url=http://deadline.com/2010/10/trio-cast-in-lena-dunhams-hbo-pilot-including-brian-williams-daughter-allison-79581/ |title=Trio Cast In Lena Dunham's HBO Pilot, Including Brian Williams' Daughter Allison |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]. |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |location=Los Angeles, California|date=October 28, 2010 |accessdate=December 28, 2011}}</ref> ''Girls'' premiered on April 15, 2012.
Williams wrote a series of [[Funny or Die]] [[sketch comedy|sketches]], in which she starred as newlywed [[Kate Middleton]],<ref name="post"/> with English actor and model [[Oliver Jackson-Cohen]] as [[Prince William, Duke of Cambridge]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.funnyordie.com/allison_williams |title=Allison Williams |website=[[Funny or Die]] |publisher=[[Gary Sanchez Productions]]|location=Los Angeles, California|accessdate=April 16, 2013}}</ref> Williams appeared as Danielle in an episode of the third season of ''[[The League]]'' titled "The Guest Bong."
Williams has appeared as a recurring character, Cheryl, in the [[CollegeHumor]] series ''[[Jake and Amir]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.collegehumor.com/video/6660383/jake-and-amir-cheryl |title=Jake and Amir / Cheryl |publisher=[[CollegeHumor]] |date=December 1, 2011 |accessdate=April 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.collegehumor.com/video/6810508/jake-and-amir-cheryl-part-2 |title=Jake and Amir / Cheryl Part 2 (starring Allison Williams) |publisher=CollegeHumor |date=August 14, 2012 |accessdate=April 16, 2013}}</ref>
On December 4, 2014 she starred in [[Peter Pan|the title role]] on [[NBC]]'s live television presentation of the musical ''[[Peter Pan Live!]]'', opposite [[Christopher Walken]] as [[Captain Hook]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Marc |last=Sneticker |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2014/07/30/allison-williams-peter-pan-live |title=Allison Williams to play Peter Pan in NBC's 'Peter Pan Live' |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]] |location=New York City|date=July 30, 2014 |accessdate=July 30, 2014}}</ref> In November 2016, Williams appeared in ''Past Forward'', a short film collaboration between [[David O. Russell]] and [[Prada]].
In 2017, Williams starred in the hit horror film ''[[Get Out]]'', directed by [[Jordan Peele]], who became convinced she was right for the role of Rose after seeing her performance in ''Peter Pan Live!'' <ref>{{cite news|first1=Patrick|last1=Hipes|title=Allison Williams To Star In Jordan Peele’s Horror Movie ‘Get Out’|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/allison-williams-get-out-jordan-peele-horror-movie-1201606920/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Eldridge Industries]]|location=Los Angeles, California|date=November 4, 2015|accessdate=May 27, 2016}}</ref>
In 2018, Williams was cast in a recurring role throughout the second and third seasons of the [[Netflix]] comedy drama series ''[[A Series of Unfortunate Events]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first1=Joe|last1=Otterson|title=Allison Williams Joins ‘A Series of Unfortunate Events’ at Netflix|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/get-out-allison-williams-a-series-of-unfortunate-events-netflix-1202731365/|accessdate=April 2, 2018|work=Variety|date=March 20, 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== Williams began dating [[Ricky Van Veen]], co-founder of [[CollegeHumor]], in 2011. They became engaged in 2014<ref>{{cite web |last=Blumm |first=K.C. |last2=Jordan |first2=Julie |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20791421,0.html |title=Allison Williams Engaged to Ricky Van Veen |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |publisher=Time |date=February 26, 2014 |accessdate=February 26, 2014}}</ref> and married on September 19, 2015 in a private ceremony in [[Saratoga, Wyoming]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/allison-williams-marries-ricky-van-veen |title=Allison Williams and Ricky Van Veen Are Married |publisher=People.com |date=September 19, 2015 |accessdate=September 19, 2015 }}</ref> [[Tom Hanks]] officiated the ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://us.hellomagazine.com/lifestyle/1201510068422/allison-williams-heavenly-honeymoon-with-ricky-van-veen/|title=Allison Williams and Ricky Van Veen's honeymoon was 'heavenly' |date=2015-10-06|accessdate=2015-10-16|publisher=[[Hello (magazine)|Hello]]|website=HELLO! US}}</ref> She and her husband live in [[Chelsea, Manhattan|Chelsea, New York]].<ref name=nyc>{{cite web |url=https://www.brickunderground.com/blog/2015/02/allison_williams_celebrity_neighbor|title=Chelsea 'Girl': Allison Williams makes her home on Manhattan's West side|publisher=Brick Underground|date=February 18, 2015}}</ref><ref name=nyc-gawker>{{cite web |url=http://defamer.gawker.com/allison-williams-might-be-the-most-boring-person-in-new-1685292170|title=Allison Williams Might Be the Most Boring Person in New York|publisher=[[Gawker]]|date=February 11, 2015}}</ref>
===Advocacy=== Williams is an ambassador for Horizons National. She led the 2016 "10 Days of Giving" campaign to raise awareness and funds for the organization's educational goals and is expected to revisit this role in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.horizonsnational.org/news/allison-williams-sets-the-stage-for-horizons-giving-day/|title=Allison Williams Sets the Stage for Horizons Giving Day|last=|first=|date=May 4, 2016|website=Horizonsnational.org|publisher=Horizons National|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=June 24, 2017}}</ref> Williams recently talked about her political views, advocacy, millennial activism, and women in Hollywood on the [[Politico]] podcast ''Women Rule''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2017/06/21/allison-williams-trump-girls-women-rule-239786|title=Allison Williams re-imagines ‘Girls’ in the Trump era|last=|first=|date=June 6, 2017|website=Politico.com|publisher=[[Politico]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=June 24, 2017}}</ref>
